name: Bi-fuel System
other_information: In simple terms, dual combustion.The bi-fuel system allows your diesel generator set to consume both diesel fuel and natural gas to operate the engine. After conversion to bi-fuel, the engine is able to operate on either 100% diesel fuel, or alternatively, on a mixture of diesel fuel and natural gas (or other methane based fuels). At no time, however, is the engine able to operate on natural gas exclusively. What are the benefits of bi-fuel? (1) Lower fuel costs by as much as 70% with today's natural gas prices (2) Extend the onsite fueling capabilities from your diesel storage tanks from 72 hours to over a week (3) Reduce emissions by burning less diesel and cleaner natural gas Ask a WPP Sales Representative for more details today.
